An administrative officer, Force Public Relations Department, SP Benjamin Hundeyin has taken over from CSP Adekunle Ajisebutu as the new Lagos State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO). Ajisebutu took over from CSP Olumuyiwa Adejobi following the Inspector-General of Police, IGP Usman Alkali Babaâ€™s approved the posting of Adejobi to the Force Public Relations Department, Force Headquarters, Abuja in August 2021. Police sources said Ajisebutu, who has spent eight months as the Lagos State PPRO, may remain in the Lagos State Police Command. His new redeployment is yet to be confirmed. 